<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-19-0559 </DOCNO><TEXT>With the advent of the standard for quarks and leptons and unified forcesthere are profound new questions for the physics of strongly interactingsystems: the nature of the nucleon, the physics of quark confinement,fundamental symmetries governing hadron decay and the effect of quarksand gluons on nuclear behavior. Of the new large facilities now plannedto respond to these questions the kaon factory is central. It uses veryintense ({similar_to}100 {mu}A) primary proton beams ({similar_to}30GeV) to generate intense secondary beams of various hadrons and leptons.</TEXT></DOC>